==============================================================================
Interoperability basis
==============================================================================

The reverse engineering and reimplementation undertaken by this
project is limited in scope and purpose to enabling interoperability
between independently-created software and the Autodesk Revit file
format. This qualifies under the interoperability exception of
17 U.S.C. § 1201(f) ("DMCA") in U.S. jurisdictions, and under
analogous exceptions in EU Directive 2009/24/EC (Articles 5 and 6)
and Australian Copyright Act s. 47D in other jurisdictions.

No effective technological measures controlling access to a
copyrighted work have been circumvented. The underlying file
container (Microsoft Compound File Binary Format) is a published
public specification; the compression (DEFLATE) is RFC 1951; neither
involves rights-management technology.

